          Site Reliability Engineer, Nielsen Marketing Cloud-1602985
            Description
           The Nielen Marketing Cloud is the leading provider of data technology powering the digital marketing ecosystem. Our customer data cloud™ provides the industry’s only unified customer profiles, which connect identities across all channels and devices – including display, video, audio, offline, mobile and smart TVs – enabling marketers to engage individuals and households with personalized messages to drive performance at scale. The Nielsen Marketing Cloud's data marketplace is the largest 3rd-party cross-device data set in the world with over 5B unique users and devices.
           Nielsen brings to bear the market’s most powerful proprietary data assets, and together we are helping the world’s biggest brands make better and faster marketing and media decisions, we are permanently disrupting the landscape of audience measurement. For more information, please visit nielsen.com, or follow us: @Nielsen.
            Position Summary:
           In our Information Technology Team at the Nielsen Marketing Cloud, we encourage bridging creativity with stability in our efforts to scale through supporting, growing, and optimizing our environment for our ever-growing community of data consumers and analyzers around the globe. We take pride in the fact that our infrastructure is unique, in that we handle over billions of queries a day, with the help of ~600 Linux servers addressing the heavy lifting and our high-performance databases handling the real-time storage demands of the Big Data Infrastructure.
           While our Infrastructure has a physical presence in 5 data centers, strategically located across US and EU, as a member of the NY team, you’ll have an opportunity to exercise your SRE skills on a global scale. The position will work closely with other team members (and across groups) to address the deployment and maintenance needs required to seamlessly ensure the environment is up and running 24/7. We’re looking for a candidate, who not only is a true Linux ninja, but has ability to serve as a Network Architect, with a deep understanding of TCP/IP, Load-Balancers, and firewalls, as well, has some light-weight MySQL DB experience. Key responsibilities for this role include but are not limited to:
           So, if you are a self-starter, highly motivated, and take pride in what you do, then this is an excellent opportunity to prove your skills in a large scale Linux environment.
            Troubleshoot and analyze hardware, networks, application, and storage/DB related issues
            Cohesively work within a team to manage the monitoring and stability of our multi-cloudColo environments
            Build, configure, and proactively automate systems and services
            Install and support in-house, open-source, and 3rd party applications throughout the technology stack
            Collaborate with our Developers and Data Scientists on design concepts to help right-size, build, scale and automate production infrastructure solutions
            Provide peer support to other SREs and End Users
            Qualifications
            Minimum Requirements:
            BS/MS in Computer Science or relevant work experience
            Minimum of 3 years of related Site Reliability Engineering experience in Unix environment
            Configuration and operational experience with firewalls, network switches, and load balancers
            Experience supporting MySQL databases
            Enthusiastic about configuration management and automation
            Solid experience in at least one administrative scripting languages, such as: Bash and/or Python
            Excellent written and verbal communication skills
           Preferred Qualifications:
            Experience with any of the following tools we like: AWS, Ansible, Zabbix, Spark, Kafka, Docker
            Comfortable working in a dynamic startup environment
           Note:
          Participation in our off-hours on-call support rotation (Required)
